<br>
E.g. Assume a mob only had a hate window of 2 people<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
TimeT:0.....1.....2.....3.....4
AtkrA:-..1..1..2..1..1..1..1..1
AtkrB:-.....3.....2.....2.....2
AtkrC:-...........4...........7
</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
At Time 2, the mob chose A&amp;B for its' hate window, come time 4 it only considers C for 7 dmg, instead of the total 11.  So despite outdamaging A &amp; B, C wouldn't draw aggro.<br>
<br>
But, like I said, this is in the past, extending the hate window size removed this problem; but it however didn't remove the old addage about fast weapons = more taunt. <p>---<BR>
